# Styling and Design Conventions

## Color System

Use the semantic color variables defined in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css):

- `text-foreground` - Primary text color
- `text-muted-foreground` - Secondary/muted text
- `text-muted` - Tertiary text
- `bg-background` - Main background
- `border-border` - Border color
- `ring-ring` - Focus ring color

## Custom Cursor Brand Colors

Use the custom cursor colors from [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts):
- `cursor-orange` - Primary brand color (#ff6b35)
- `cursor-orange-light` - Light variant (#ff8c5a)
- `cursor-orange-dark` - Dark variant (#e55a2b)
- `cursor-dark` - Pure black (#000000)
- `cursor-gray` - Dark gray (#0a0a0a)
- `cursor-gray-light` - Light gray (#1a1a1a)
- `cursor-gray-medium` - Medium gray (#27272a)

## Spacing and Layout

- Use the custom spacing scale: `18` (4.5rem), `88` (22rem), `128` (32rem)
- Follow the 8px grid system for consistent spacing
- Use semantic spacing classes: `space-y-*`, `gap-*`, `p-*`, `m-*`

## Border Radius

Use the CSS variable-based border radius:
- `rounded-lg` - Uses `var(--radius)` (0.5rem)
- `rounded-md` - Uses `calc(var(--radius) - 2px)`
- `rounded-sm` - Uses `calc(var(--radius) - 4px)`

## Animations

Use the custom animations defined in [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts):
- `animate-fade-in` - Fade in effect
- `animate-slide-up` - Slide up from bottom
- `animate-scale-in` - Scale in effect

## Focus and Interaction States

- Always include focus states with `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2`
- Use `focus:ring-ring` for consistent focus color
- Include hover states for interactive elements
- Use `active:scale-[0.98]` for button press feedback

## Typography

- Use the Inter font family (loaded in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css))
- Leverage font-feature-settings for better typography
- Use the Typography component instead of raw text classes